# Pinned scanner versions (ADR-0028).
#
# Format:  <name> <version>
#
# Integrity is verified at install time against upstream-published artefacts,
# not against locally-recorded SHAs:
#
# - trivy:   we download ``trivy_<version>_checksums.txt`` from the GitHub
#            release (published and signed by aquasec/trivy CI), grep out
#            the row for the platform-specific archive we just downloaded,
#            and verify before extracting. A single ``.scanner-versions``
#            SHA can never work here — every platform tarball has a
#            different digest, and locally-pinned digests would need a
#            row per (os, arch) combination.
#
# - semgrep: installed via pip from PyPI into a private venv. Integrity
#            comes from PyPI's per-wheel digests + TLS pin; the previously
#            recorded "binary SHA" was actually the SHA of a dynamically
#            generated wrapper script (always different) and was therefore
#            meaningless. We instead verify by running ``semgrep --version``
#            and asserting it matches the pinned version.
#
# To bump:
#   1. Bump the version below.
#   2. Run ``scripts/install-scanners.sh`` once to confirm the upstream
#      checksums file still verifies clean.
#   3. Commit the bump.

trivy 0.70.0
semgrep 1.70.0
